<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. Vanhornia eucnemidarum Crawford, 1909 (female, specimens from USA) A habitus, dorsal view B body, dorsal view C body, lateral view D antennae, head and mesosoma, ventral view E right mandible, lateral view F head and mesoscutum, dorso-lateral view G head, front view H mesosoma, lateral view I metasoma, dorsal view J metasoma, ventral view K wings." , "Figure 3. Vanhornia quizhouensis (He & Chu, 1990) (female, holotype) A habitus, dorsal view B mandible, ventro-lateral view C head, front view D head, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F mesosoma, lateral view G metasoma, dorsal view H metasoma, lateral view I wings." , "Figure 2. Vanhornia yurii sp. nov. (female, holotype) A wings B metasomal tergite 6, posterior view C metasoma, dorsal view D metasoma, ventral view E metasoma, lateral view." , "Figure 1. Vanhornia yurii sp. nov. (female, holotype) A habitus, dorsal view B mandible, antero-lateral view C head, lateral view D head, front view E head, dorsal view F antenna G mesosoma, dorsal view H mesosoma, lateral view I hind leg." , "Figure 8. Map of distribution of Vanhornia in Eurasia. Green spot - V. yurii sp. nov., blue spots - V. leileri, yellow spots - V. quizhouensis, red spot - specimen from South Korea determined as V. eucnemidarum (Choi & Lee, 2012)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469455" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469456" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469460" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469453" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469454" .

